    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Ultrastructural localization of endogenous Rab5 in CA1 neurons of rat hippocampus.\"\n- \" Most synaptic Rab5 immunolabeling was found in the postsynaptic terminal (~75%; Figure 1A, arrows; Figure 1B, \"POST\"). Furthermore, we found that postsynaptic Rab5 labeling was predominantly located outside of the postsynaptic density (PSD) on lateral extrasynaptic membranes (Figure 1B, \"Memb.\"), roughly 100-300 nm away from the edge of the PSD (Figure 1C). This localization fits well with \"endocytic hotspots\" previously described lateral to the PSD (Blanpied et al., 2002; Petralia et al., 2003; Racz et al., 2004).\"\n\nNote: the imaging data by itself does not resolve the endocytic zone. The rest of the paper shows a role of Rab5 in AMPAR endocytosis and the localization lateral of the PSD is suggestive of the postsynaptic endocytic zone.. Experimental description: - \"Ultrastructural localization of endogenous Rab5 in CA1 neurons of rat hippocampus.\"",
